Peter Obi, the presidential candidate of the Labour Party (LP), and Datti Baba-Ahmed, his running mate, held campaign rallies in Gombe and Adamawa on Tuesday. The LP candidates also visited Daniel Shaga, the paramount ruler of Hamma Bachama, in his palace in Adamawa. Also present at the rally in Adamawa was Aisha Yesufu, an activist, as well as spouses of the LP candidates. Below are pictures.                       